# Next.js App Router Standards

## Components

- Server Components by default. Only add `"use client"` when the component needs hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers.
- Push the client boundary to leaf components. Never mark a page or layout as client.
- Use `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx` for route segments with async data.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — entire page is client
"use client";
export default function Page() { /* fetches data in useEffect */ }

// ✅ GOOD — server page, client leaf
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getData();
  return <InteractiveWidget data={data} />;
}
```

## Data and Mutations

- Fetch data in Server Components. No `useEffect` + `fetch` for initial page data.
- Use Server Actions for all mutations. API Route Handlers only for webhooks and external callbacks.
- Call `revalidatePath` or `revalidateTag` after every mutation.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — unvalidated action
export async function createTask(data: any) {
  await db.task.create({ data });
}

// ✅ GOOD — validated, auth-checked, revalidated
export async function createTask(input: CreateTaskInput): Promise<ActionResult<{ id: string }>> {
  const session = await requireAuth();
  const parsed = createTaskSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) return { success: false, error: "Invalid input" };
  const task = await db.task.create({ data: { ...parsed.data, createdById: session.user.id } });
  revalidatePath("/tasks");
  return { success: true, data: { id: task.id } };
}
```

## Feature Architecture

- Code lives in `src/features/<name>/` with `actions/`, `components/`, `schemas/`, `types/`, `lib/`.
- Route files in `src/app/` are thin — compose feature components, no business logic.
- Never import across features. Compose in the `app/` layer instead.

## Forms

- React Hook Form with `zodResolver` for all user-facing forms.
- Share Zod schemas between form resolver and Server Action.

## Types and Validation

- Zod schemas are the single source of truth. Derive types with `z.infer<typeof schema>`.
- Check auth in every Server Action before mutations.
- Return `ActionResult<T>` from actions. Do not throw for expected failures.
